cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR

This paper focuses on the automatic identification of fake news in online media outlets, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for collecting and analyzing online news data, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms for fake news detection indicates cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of online security and trustworthiness, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
